helptext.en: Samples Collected - Enter a non-existent character string to prompt new sample entry.

Location Descriptor - enter a brief description of the general location in 40 characters or less.

Detailed Location - provide a description of the fossil location such as: 1) the distance and cardinal direction (north, east, south, west) where the fossil site lies in relation to a specific geographic feature; 2) metres above the base of a geological section; 3) relationship of the fossil layer to a prominent layer such as a coal seam or thick sandstone; 4) elevation; or 5) if the fossil comes from talus or scree.

instructions.en: If needed, add additional information about the fossil collection event.
